{
  "texts": [
    "Introduction\"When we think about [AI], we need to put human dignity, human well-being-human jobs-in the centre of consideration.\"-Dr.",
    "Fei Fei Li [1] Software systems enabled by artificial intelligence (AIenabled systems) 1 are increasingly used for various purposes in real-world settings [3][4][5].",
    "For example, AI-enabled systems are deciding who gets hired [6], fired, or promoted [7], who gets a loan or life insurance [8] and who receives which medical treatment [9].",
    "AI-enabled systems are also driving cars [10], delivering care to elderly patients [11,12], diagnosing health symptoms [13], cleaning airports [14], and managing a city's waste [15].Yet, AI-enabled systems are still \"emerging technologies\" that, despite their potential for society, also come with the significant risk of negative consequences [5].",
    "One particularly severe example is the childcare benefits scandal (\"toeslagenaffaire\") in the Netherlands, where a selflearning algorithm used by Dutch tax authorities wrongly accused thousands of families of fraud, disproportionately targeting ethnic minorities, and resulted in devastating financial problems for those families [16]."
  ]
}